To my younger self… I love you. I love little Leslie so much the things I went through as a child was a lot. I had to be a little grown up as a child. I want the best life for my kids. No child deserves to hurt. I worked very hard to get to where I am. And I deserve every piece of it. I won’t let anyone tell me otherwise I won’t let anyone put me down. There are things that I can’t control and the hurt will always be there but it’s less and less each time and the people around me and my kids fill my life 🫶 it feels beautiful to finally have the freedom to do what I love and leave the shop to go to the gym or be able to run errands and not be forced to work like I had in the past. 
I want you to know that no matter what you are going through you are loved and you deserve to feel love ❤️ I believe that if you work hard towards a dream you can do anything ✨✨✨✨ we are capable of wonderful things 🫶🫶🫶 #love #selflove #healing #heal #spirituality #spiritualawakening #lovequotes #eternal #crystals #crystalshop #crystalshopping #community #together #togetherforever

27… When I lost and found myself… it’s not my birthday yet but as I am getting closer to 28 I am reflecting & 27 will always be a year I will remember and hold close to me. Last year I wasn’t in the best place but it led me to where I am. I learned to listen to my inner voice, to get away from people that don’t deserve my energy, & to not react even when I wanted to. I feel the divine feminine energy in me and I hope that I can help more find that power within themselves. You are a strong and a powerful being capable of amazing things. Society made it hard for me to love myself and to accept me for me but today I love everything about myself the good and the bad 🌹 🥀 & I wouldn’t change a thing 🫶🥰

I am excited to see what the future holds. I did a little mini photo shoot on the day of my birthday. I wanted to do it outside because in nature I feel at home plus the sun ☀️ is always the best light. Shout out to my amazing photographer, Alberto, and thank you for the beautiful pearl chocker and matching pearl bracelet. Made @gemzandboardz 🤍I couldn’t choose one photo so here you get to see it all. ✨ ✨ I will continue to love myself and allow to be loved, to be surrounded by beautiful people who love me and experience life with them. You will forever be missed you will forever be loved. 7 years ago today I lost you. 7 years ago today I thought I would not be able to make it I felt like I couldn’t breathe like I didn’t want to go on without you. To loose someone you love and not even imagining it is what hurt the most. I was left alone with a 18  old month boy. I couldn’t see a future but somehow I made it and here I am. I know you are looking out for us and will always be there. Rest In Peace Giovanny Anthony Quintanilla. Until we meet again! Forever in our hearts 💕 so to those that lost someone, it might not feel like it but it will get easier and you will smile again remember they are always next to us and are never really gone

Vertebral artery dissection ❤️‍🩹Update: 3 months after diagnosis ✨✨✨ Today I found out that my injury is not healed and that it can take  6 months to heal but if it doesn’t heal by then it can be there forever. Forever was never an option. I can’t lift more than 20 pounds, I have to Avoid yoga, golf, roller coasters, bungee jumping, or other activities that involve hyperextension or twisting of the neck. I don’t want to live like this forever. I miss dying my hair red, I miss going to the gym 💪 and working out lifting gave me power. I hate feeling tired sometimes because of the medication or the injury I hate not being myself. But I am determined to find the other option and starting February I will step back from work and actually rest, and find natural remedies, and be more with nature. I refuse to be sick forever. #healing #heal #update #lifeupdate #spiritually #awaken

After getting my diagnosis in October of my vertebrae artery dissection, I had to take blood thinners which meant I couldn’t take seamoss or work out like I wanted to by lifting heavy. However this January I was told my injury didn’t heal and that it may never heal. But I refuse to the idea that it may never heal. The doctors  took me off the blood thinners and it has been helping how I feel. The blood thinners made me feel not like myself and I was entering a maybe depressive state. I have decided to go back to being me regardless of my injury, of course I still have to take it easy but I am determined to get back to my routine. Today is also the first day I am no longer working my day job. So I can honestly do whatever I want and I am choosing me. I am starting with seamoss gel from @euphoricmoss to give me the energy and push I need to start my day and a bunch of more benefits from the seamoss.
